radiographic_examinations.findings: The gallbladder is partially collapsed with thickening of the fundal portion of the gallbladder wall and focal punctate echogenicities consistent with a fundal adenomyoma. No gallstones are visualized. There is no intrahepatic biliary dilatation, and the extrahepatic common bile duct is normal measuring 0.6 cm. The visualized portions of the pancreas are within normal limits.
